The paper deals with approximation algorithms for Maxcut, which is a well-studied problem in computer science. The use of random walks and graph partitioning techniques suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper's focus on approximation algorithms and its mention of a weak local graph partitioning procedure suggests that it may also belong to the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
